['text':' SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0 ','line_number':1,'multiline':True]['text':' Static buffer policy.','line_number':15,'multiline':False]['text':'  This buffer is fixed, size must not be changed','line_number':34,'multiline':False]['text':' This allocator allocates a reference counted buffer which is used by v2_decoder_t','line_number':44,'multiline':False]['text':' to use zero-copy msg::init_data to create messages with memory from this buffer as','line_number':45,'multiline':False]['text':' data storage.','line_number':46,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':47,'multiline':False]['text':' The buffer is allocated with a reference count of 1 to make sure that is is alive while','line_number':48,'multiline':False]['text':' decoding messages. Otherwise, it is possible that e.g. the first message increases the count','line_number':49,'multiline':False]['text':' from zero to one, gets passed to the user application, processed in the user thread and deleted','line_number':50,'multiline':False]['text':' which would then deallocate the buffer. The drawback is that the buffer may be allocated longer','line_number':51,'multiline':False]['text':' than necessary because it is only deleted when allocate is called the next time.','line_number':52,'multiline':False]['text':' Create an allocator for a maximum number of messages','line_number':58,'multiline':False]['text':' Allocate a new buffer','line_number':64,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':65,'multiline':False]['text':' This releases the current buffer to be bound to the lifetime of the messages','line_number':66,'multiline':False]['text':' created on this buffer.','line_number':67,'multiline':False]['text':' force deallocation of buffer.','line_number':70,'multiline':False]['text':' Give up ownership of the buffer. The buffer's lifetime is now coupled to','line_number':73,'multiline':False]['text':' the messages constructed on top of it.','line_number':74,'multiline':False]['text':' Return pointer to the first message data byte.','line_number':83,'multiline':False]['text':' Return pointer to the first byte of the buffer.','line_number':86,'multiline':False]